3. There is no code in the workspace populating those two report arrays:
- Search only finds usage inside app/(dashboard)/reports.tsx/reports.tsx), not any Firebase subscription writing to them.

4. TypeScript already flags this:
- app/(dashboard)/reports.tsx#L515/reports.tsx#L515) has compile errors: Property premonitoringReadings does not exist on AppState, and Property gasReadings does not exist on AppState.

5. Firebase itself is configured and used elsewhere:
- Firebase config exists in firebase.ts.
- Live listeners for workers/alerts/sensors are wired in app/(dashboard)/overview.tsx#L685/overview.tsx#L685) through sensorService.ts.
- A direct pre-monitor path is used in overview card at app/(dashboard)/overview.tsx#L579/overview.tsx#L579), but that is not feeding Reports.

